{
  "texts": [
    "Guided by the task loss, we can efficiently learn mapping f w ∶ PD x → V x and automatically answer the question of \"which family of vectorizations should best work for the given task\".",
    "Handling PDs by neural networks is the focus of many deep topological embedding studies.",
    "Generally, PDs deep vectorization layers should be continuous and permutation invariant with respect to the input.",
    "The latter requirement is motivated by the set nature of the persistence diagram.",
    "Hofer et al. (2017 Hofer et al. (, 2019)) introduced the first learnable deep vectorization of PDs."
  ]
}